OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1779520003
OL,3,CReality TV risks 'crossing line into
OL,4,Cexploitation', former Ofcom chair says
OL,6,FTwo women told the programme they were
OL,7,Fallegedly raped by their on-screen
OL,8,Fpartners during filming, while a third
OL,9,Faccused her on-screen partner of
OL,10,Fsexual misconduct. All three men deny
OL,11,Fthe allegations.
OL,13,FCommenting on the MAFS scandal, Lord
OL,14,FGrade said producers are in danger of
OL,15,Fputting the public into more and more
OL,16,Fconfrontational and emotional
OL,17,Fsituations as shows are "creeping so
OL,18,Fclose to the line, we're tipping over
OL,19,Fit".
OL,26,@yD@YOU{D@CO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/10
