OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1779520003
OL,3,CReality TV risks 'crossing line into
OL,4,Cexploitation', former Ofcom chair says
OL,6,FHe told Times Radio: "The alarm bells
OL,7,Fring when you see what a suite of
OL,8,Fprotocols and duty of care measures
OL,9,Fhave to be put in place to protect the
OL,10,Fpublic.
OL,12,F"And these protocols are getting
OL,13,Fbigger and bigger as the risks get
OL,14,Fgreater and greater.
OL,16,F"And that's a real danger sign for me,
OL,17,Ffor these reality shows crossing a
OL,18,Fline into exploitation and taking
OL,19,Frisks with the public's mental health
OL,20,Fin ways that they shouldn't be doing."
OL,26,@nD@VOUtD@AOUxD@AOU|D@fO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/10
