OL,3,CReality TV risks 'crossing line into
OL,4,Cexploitation', former Ofcom chair says
OL,6,FLord Grade added: "Many reality shows
OL,7,Fare wonderful. I mean, Traitors and
OL,8,Flots of other shows and even Big
OL,9,FBrother, I thought was fine.
OL,11,F"But we are in danger as the heat gets
OL,12,Fturned up and the public are put into
OL,13,Fmore and more confrontational,
OL,14,Femotional situations, which, you know,
OL,15,Feven with all the will in the world
OL,16,Fand their informed consent to go on
OL,17,Fthe show, they could never have any
OL,18,Fidea what they were getting themselves
OL,19,Finto."
OL,26,@nD@SOUsD@AOU{D@FO]
