OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1779520003
OL,3,CReality TV risks 'crossing line into
OL,4,Cexploitation', former Ofcom chair says
OL,6,F"I mean, up to now shows were just
OL,7,Fabout the right side of the line, but
OL,8,Fwe're now creeping so close to the
OL,9,Fline, I think we're tipping over it,"
OL,10,Fhe added.
OL,12,FIn a letter to The Times, the former
OL,13,Fcontroller of BBC One wrote: "Each new
OL,14,Fformat seems to bring us closer and
OL,15,Fcloser to that abyss."
OL,26,@nD@AOUqD@eO]uD@^OUwD@VO]
