OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1779520003
OL,3,CReality TV risks 'crossing line into
OL,4,Cexploitation', former Ofcom chair says
OL,6,FHe added: "As a former broadcaster I
OL,7,Fwould urge broadcasters, in assessing
OL,8,Fnew formats, to ask themselves 'If we
OL,9,Fneed this unprecedented suite of
OL,10,Fprotections for contestants, is this
OL,11,Freally exploitation?'
OL,13,F"The answer is easy: don't make the
OL,14,Fshow."
OL,16,FChannel 4 has said its Married At
OL,17,FFirst Sight (MAFS) spin-off show
OL,18,Fremains in pre-production.
OL,26,@nD@KOUuD@AOUvD@FO]
